            <div id="dsq-comment-message-131" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Really? I change my mind on questions of economics from time to time, often in response to new evidence and without a crisis of the soul. And I don&#8217;t even think I am particularly meta-rational. Cognitive biases are indeed severe, but that is why the meta-rational exercise is worthwhile.</p>
</div>
