            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-158" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-158" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Based on my participation in various epistemically complicated debate settings, I think this ignores a certain complication: when you&#8217;re a lone meta-rational person in the company of dogmatists, your honesty doesn&#8217;t end up serving the truth. You just get walked right over because your words lack a certain punch behind them. Countering dogmatism with dogmatism creates a contrived sense of balance where bystanders at least realize both sides make a claim to being right at the expense of the credibility of the other. Although I don&#8217;t agree with him on everything, I see Krugman as someone engaging in this fire against fire strategy.</p>
</div>
