            <div id="dsq-comment-message-193" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Rejecting the truth does not invalidate it. Meta-rational thinkers are truth seekers. The inability of dogmatics to accept truth doesn&#8217;t make it false. Being right is sometimes bad for the individual, but it doesn&#8217;t change the nature of the truth. Ignaz Semmelweis is an excellent example of truth being trumped by convention. Only history has vindicated the poor fellow, but that&#8217;s not a credible reason to abandon or ignore meta-rationality.</p>
